Стивен Ван Зандт (англ. Steven Van Zandt; 22 ноября 1950, Винтром, Массачусетс) — италоамериканский актёр, музыкант и продюсер.

Steven Van Zandt (born November 22, 1950) is an American musician, songwriter, arranger, record producer, actor, and radio disc jockey, who frequently goes by the stage names Little Steven or Miami Steve. He is a member of Bruce Springsteen's E Street Band, in which he plays guitar and mandolin, and has acted in television dramas The Sopranos (1999–2007), in which he played the character Silvio Dante, and Lilyhammer (2012–present), in which he plays the character Frank "The Fixer" Tagliano.

Steven Van Zandt (surnommé Little Steven ou Miami Steve) est un auteur-compositeur, guitariste, producteur et acteur américain né le 22 novembre 1950 à Boston.Il est marié à Maureen Van Zandt depuis le 31 décembre 1982.

Steven Van Zandt (* 22. November 1950 als Steven Lento in Winthrop, Massachusetts) ist ein US-amerikanischer Rockmusiker, Schauspieler und Radiomoderator. Bekannt wurde er als Gitarrist in Bruce Springsteens E Street Band und als Schauspieler in der Fernsehserie Die Sopranos. Er ist seit 1982 mit Maureen Van Zandt verheiratet.

Steven Van Zandt (Winthrop, 22 novembre 1950) è un musicista, cantante e attore statunitense , conosciuto anche come Little Steven, in onore di Little Richard, o come Miami Steve, soprannome datogli da alcuni amici per il fatto che pare soffrisse sempre il freddo (Miami è una delle città più calde degli Stati Uniti d'America).Deve la sua fama soprattutto al fatto di aver suonato la chitarra e il mandolino nella E Street Band, la band di Bruce Springsteen, del quale è tuttora collaboratore.La breve ma intensa carriera di attore televisivo (1999-2007) nel ruolo di Silvio Dante nella pluripremiata serie televisiva dell'HBO I Soprano lo ha reso un volto celebre del piccolo schermo e uno dei personaggi più amati dello show.

Steven Van Zandt, geboren als Steven Lento (Winthrop, Massachusetts, 22 november 1950) is een Amerikaans musicus, acteur en radiodiskjockey. Van Zandt treedt ook op onder de namen Little Steven of Miami Steve en werkt als songwriter, arrangeur en producent. Zo produceerde hij onder andere het in 1992 verschenen album 'Better Days' voor Southside Johnny & the Asbury Jukes.

Steven Lento (Winthrop, 22 de novembro de 1950), mais conhecido como Steven Van Zandt, é um cantautor, músico, produtor musical, ator e DJ norte-americano, que frequentemente também usa os nomes artísticos Little Steve e Miami Steve. Ele é membro da E Street Band, onde toca guitarra e bandolim, e também já atuou nas séries de televisão The Sopranos e Lilyhammer.

Steven Van Zandt (n. 22 de noviembre de 1950 en Boston, Massachusetts) es un músico, arreglista, productor musical, actor y pinchadiscos de radio italoamericano, también conocido como Little Steven o Miami Steve. Musicalmente es conocido internacionalmente por ser el guitarrista de la E Street Band, la banda de Bruce Springsteen, a la que perteneció desde 1975 (con Born to Run) hasta 1984, año en que decidió separarse y comenzar su carrera en solitario con su banda Little Steven and The Disciples of Soul, aunque luego regresó en 1995. Como actor trabajó en la mítica serie de televisión Los Soprano, interpretando al consigliere Silvio Dante, brazo derecho de Tony Soprano; y desde 2012 protagoniza la serie noruego-americana Lilyhammer. Es también productor y director desde 2002 del programa radial, Little Steven's Underground Garage.

Steven Van Zandt (born November 22, 1950) is an American musician, songwriter, arranger, record producer, actor, and radio disc jockey, who frequently goes by the stage names Little Steven or Miami Steve. He is a member of Bruce Springsteen's E Street Band, in which he plays guitar and mandolin, and has acted in television dramas The Sopranos (1999–2007), in which he played the character Silvio Dante, and Lilyhammer (2012–present), in which he plays the character Frank "The Fixer" Tagliano. Van Zandt also had his own solo band called "Little Steven and The Disciples of Soul" in the 1980s. In 2014, Van Zandt was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame as a member of the E Street Band.
